	   <tr><td colspan=2>What a weird item here.&nbsp;&nbsp;Basically, from what I understand.. agility deals in damage avoidance.  So 100% of your armor class from agility is damage avoidance armor class, and zero percent of your raw armor class deals in damage avoidance, but rather damage mitigation.  For high level charachters getting quad hit for 850, I don't think 18 raw AC is a good trade off at all for 35 agility.  Even if max agility only effects the miss ratio by 1%, it's still doing alot more than 50 raw ac when you're already 300 raw ac over the soft cap.  As a caster, your armor class is going to be so low anyways, you'll get hit everytime no matter what, might as well go for resist gear and keep your fingers crossed as a caster.  As a high level tank.. that can get up to 1500ac (with a soft cap at 1100), I would much rather have 7ac in damage avoidance than 30ac in damage mitigation, especially since agility is quite hard to come by as is, without having to sacrifice to much already.  Dex also affects crits, and for casters it will effect fizzles.. plus casters would rather not get hit than hit as well... this thing basically sucks.. that's just my opinion..  Spend the 2k on some planes jewelery instead.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
