	   <tr><td colspan=2>"I'm pretty sure Dex affects how often you land blows and I know Agi affects AC. This item basically makes you hit less, while giving you the same AC as before"<br><br>I don't believe dex does not affect how often you land blows. Even if it does, the effect of stats aside from a few are very very minor. It does somewhat affect the rate at which you learn certain skills. If you were to log the hits/misses on a certain mobs of the same type and same level for say, ten fights, with&nbsp;&nbsp;high dex and do the same with low dex I bet you would hit for roughly the same percentage. Agility is a different matter. So long as your net agi is above 75 then you will take no large ac penalty. The majority of players can afford to lose 35agi. In my own experience, one ac is equal to roughly 5 to 8 points of agility. So the most you can lose from 35 agi is about 7 points of ac (provided your final agi is above 75). This still leaves you with a gain of about 11ac points. There is also the stat nerf for those of us who have been around since the beginning or near beginning. Verant nerfed the effectiveness of stats a while ago to equalize the classes more and provide a more common ground regardless of how you chose your stats when you made your character.<br><br>This is an AWESOME earring. Speaking as an enchanter who wears a lot of ac/hp gear I can say that I'd love to get my hands on one of these. The loss of 35dex is negligable to a pure caster who has no business meleeing and the loss of 35agi will still not be much of an ac loss. You'll still be ahead, way ahead, in ac points. <br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
