	   <tr><td colspan=2>Geesh - everyone has part of right - here's how it actually works.<br><br>The part about the agility loss equalling about 7 ac is right. however, based on your defense skill, you'll get much more than 18 ac out of it - more closer to 24-36 depending on your level, final agility, etc. so net AC (on your total AC) will be around the 20-25 range - damn good for an earring, about the equivalent of an item with 12ac or so.<br><br>Now as far as Agility goes: Agility modifies armor class by a small amount. Agility's main function is modifying dodge/parry/riposte/block rates, which will be lowered by this. Agility dropping below 75 is bad if you go critical since it will drop AC significantly.<br><br>Dex: Dexterity does *not* affect how often you hit in melee. it *does* affect how often you hit with ranged attacks (bow/throw). It *does* affect how you learn combat skills. And most importantly for a caster, it affects your ability to channel spells.<br><br>Hope that clears a few misconceptions, and by the way, it has been officially stated that the "book" may not be entirely correct, or that things have changed since it was printed<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
