	   <tr><td colspan=2>i ama 43 lvl monk and during lvl 40(after my stats maxed for that lvl) i did some testing using a log parcer for monks while switching between 2- 6ac/65 hp rings and 2- 6 dex/6agi rings...this was done while fighting uthorks in eastern wastes, no buffs other than haste and sow were accepted over the 1-2 hour time spans. results were this:<br>Defence: <br>misses stayed the same 41%<br>avoidance(dodge/block/reposite)went 2-3 percent with agi dex rings<br>mob hits wend down 2-3 percnet with dex agi rings<br>Offence:<br>hit/miss was unaffected<br>more off and blows were attempted with dex/agi rings on and i knoticed more 3x and 4x attacks with dex/agi rings on<br><br>thease results lead me to beleave(along with results from other times while agi or dex buffed) that dex doesnt influence your chance to hit, but does affect duel wield and double attacks skills, while agi does affect ur avoidance so ac a monk i would never use this earing as 35 dex and agi is just too much to lose<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
